<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9753655156848></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9753655156848><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?id=3530&mid=9753655156848>Hunt Information</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?id=3530&mid=9753655156848#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 27th 5:51 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alright, here's what I learned from my experience.  I'm a level 50 bard, with appropriate equipment.  I started working my way down into Sol A, using my invis.  The majority of goblins don't see through it, some of the shamans do.  At 50, they'll still attack me, but I avoided the majority of them pretty easily.  As I got closer to the castle, I found that the clockworks see through invis as well, and attacked me.  I killed some fairly easily, and supposed that they didn't like me due to the fact I had killed some before while helping a paladin friend in his quests.  In reality, I found they were attacking me because I was in dark elf form at the time.  In my normal half-elven state, they were dubious to me.  I proceeded to use a song that increases my faction with the target to bring me to amiable with them, at which point I was able to walk all the way to the room where the elemental spawns.<br><br>Now then, there are 4 stationary clockworks inside the room, and some various gnomes and the like outside.  All of them were green to me at 50, and amiable at this point as well.  There is a wandering clockwork that is the placeholder for the elemental.  When I attacked him, none of the other clockworks tried to help him.  I fought him inside the room itself, and killed him easily.  Different types of clockworks spawn, they aren't much of a problem.  Spawn time is around 19 min.  Eventually, the elemental will spawn.  It seems random to me from what I saw.<br><br>The elemental aggroed on me immediately.  If you get too near the edges of the room, the gnomes on the outside may well cast buffs on him, which is annoying.  I fought him inside the room, and had no problems.  He has a damage shield that will put quite a hurting on melee types, so make sure to hit him with cancel magic.  After this, it was a melee fight for me.  As a bard, my melee is pathetic, and I ended up having to mez him and then heal myself, after which I killed him with no other problems.  He hit me a couple times for double 70s.  I was slowing down his attack during the fight, so in actuality, he's a pretty good fight for melee types.<br><br>The first time I killed him he had a no-drop ruby that didn't have any distinguishing stats or the like, I assume its for a quest of some sort.  The second time I killed him, I got the pendant.  It took about 4 hours between spawns, so get comfy.  After that, I invised and headed out, unfortunately I took a wrong turn and ended up in a room with a bunch of blazing elementals.  They happen to see through invis.. caused a few problems.  Anyways, hope this helps out.  Good luck.<br><br>Druevan Valkyren<br>Wandering Bard of Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
